        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(raft): add CLI wake bridge channel",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw users cannot currently connect an agent to Raft's local CLI bridge. Raft can notify a local process that messages are pending, but there is no supported OpenClaw channel to route that wake signal to an agent.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdds Raft as an official external channel plugin. The plugin starts Raft's local `agent bridge`, accepts only authenticated content-free wake hints on loopback, persists replay protection in the plugin state database, and dispatches a serial agent turn that directs the agent to read and respond through the Raft CLI. It intentionally does not treat Raft wake payloads as message content or implement a synthetic outbound transport.\n\nThe bridge now implements the current Raft CLI wake contract: an accepted wake returns a stable runtime-session identifier, and the authenticated activity-drain endpoint acknowledges an empty batch. This follows direct inspection of the installed Raft CLI bridge implementation.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators can configure a Raft profile through `channels.raft`, start the gateway, and have an OpenClaw agent wake when Raft has pending work. Multiple named accounts are supported, as are environment-backed default profiles.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/raft/src/accounts.test.ts extensions/raft/src/channel.test.ts extensions/raft/src/gateway.test.ts test/official-channel-catalog.test.ts test/plugin-npm-package-manifest.test.ts src/config/validation.channel-metadata.test.ts src/plugins/manifest-registry.test.ts`\n  - 119 tests passed across four Vitest shards on the rebased head.\n- `node scripts/generate-plugin-inventory-doc.mjs --check`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/generate-bundled-channel-config-metadata.ts --check`\n- `node scripts/generate-npm-shrinkwrap.mjs --check --package-dir extensions/raft`\n- `node scripts/report-test-temp-creations.mjs --base origin/main --head HEAD --fail-on-findings`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --engine codex`\n  - clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Blacksmith Testbox typechecked the current bridge-protocol change. Its first changed-gate run found one test lint violation, fixed in `73e45bfad9`; a subsequent local-Testbox retry was polluted by shared-worktree `node_modules` sync, so this PR does not claim that retry as clean full-gate proof.\n- An authenticated current Raft CLI profile started the actual `agent bridge` against the plugin's loopback gateway. A real Raft DM (`wake test`) produced a server-delivered, authenticated content-free wake that the bridge recorded as harness-accepted and wake-injected with the runtime session returned by the plugin.\n- The native prepare gate completed `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` and `pnpm build`; `pnpm check` is blocked by three pre-existing `origin/main` Discord declaration errors for `formatRealtimeLogPreview`. This PR does not touch that file.\n",
